{"parse":{"title":"Calvin Thomas (critical theorist)","pageid":10556958,"revid":788772097,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other people with the same name, see <a href=\"/wiki/Calvin_Thomas_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Calvin Thomas (disambiguation)\">Calvin Thomas (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<p><b>Calvin Thomas</b> is an <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Academic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Academic\">academic</a> who works in the fields of <a href=\"/wiki/Critical_theory\" title=\"Critical theory\">critical theory</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_modern_literature\" title=\"History of modern literature\">modern</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Postmodern_literature\" title=\"Postmodern literature\">postmodern literature</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Culture\" title=\"Culture\">culture</a>.  He is a professor at <a href=\"/wiki/Georgia_State_University\" title=\"Georgia State University\">Georgia State University</a>. His writings have focused on <a href=\"/wiki/Gender\" title=\"Gender\">gender</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Sexual_identity\" title=\"Sexual identity\">sexuality</a> and the body, with an especial interest in <a href=\"/wiki/Heterosexuality\" title=\"Heterosexuality\">\"straight\"</a> responses to <a href=\"/wiki/Queer_theory\" title=\"Queer theory\">queer theory</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Calvin_Thomas_(critical_theorist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Thomas, Calvin (1998). <i>Male Matters</i>. Champaign: University of Illinois Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-06500-X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-252-06500-X\">0-252-06500-X</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Male+Matters&amp;rft.place=Champaign&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=0-252-06500-X&amp;rft.aulast=Thomas&amp;rft.aufirst=Calvin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+Thomas+%28critical+theorist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Thomas, Calvin (2000). <i>Straight with a Twist: Queer Theory and the Subject of Heterosexuality</i>. Champaign: University of Illinois Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-252-06813-0\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-252-06813-0\">0-252-06813-0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Straight+with+a+Twist%3A+Queer+Theory+and+the+Subject+of+Heterosexuality&amp;rft.place=Champaign&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Illinois+Press&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=0-252-06813-0&amp;rft.aulast=Thomas&amp;rft.aufirst=Calvin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+Thomas+%28critical+theorist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Thomas, Calvin (2008). <i>Masculinity, Psychoanalysis, Straight Queer Theory: Essays on Abjection in Literature, Mass Culture, and Film</i>. New York: Palgrave/Macmillan. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-230-60008-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-230-60008-5\">0-230-60008-5</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Masculinity%2C+Psychoanalysis%2C+Straight+Queer+Theory%3A+Essays+on+Abjection+in+Literature%2C+Mass+Culture%2C+and+Film&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Palgrave%2FMacmillan&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=0-230-60008-5&amp;rft.aulast=Thomas&amp;rft.aufirst=Calvin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACalvin+Thomas+%28critical+theorist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>Thomas, Calvin (2013). <i>Ten Lessons in Theory: An Introduction to Theoretical Writing.</i> London: Bloomsbury Academic. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/1623564026\" title=\"Special:BookSources/1623564026\">1623564026</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Calvin_Thomas_(critical_theorist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.english.gsu.edu/people.php?req=thomas\">Calvin Thomas web page</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Georgia_State_University\" title=\"Georgia State University\">Georgia State University</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><span style=\"vertical-align: middle; background:transparent\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_the_United_States.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of United States\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/30px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"16\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_th